      <p>
        <s>The extract <name type="misc">Lady Macbeth persuades her husband</name> is from <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="title">Macbeth</ref>, <choice><orig>Act</orig><reg>act</reg></choice> 1, <choice><orig>Scene</orig><reg>scene</reg></choice> 7 and is written from <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="author"><choice><orig>Shakespear</orig><reg>Shakespeare</reg></choice></ref>.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>The <choice><orig>Scene</orig><reg>scene</reg></choice> shows a conversation between <name type="person">Lady Macbeth</name> and her husband <name type="person">Macbeth</name>, the future king of <name type="geo">Scotland</name>.</s>
        <s>But <name type="person">Macbeth</name> wants to be <choice><orig>King</orig><reg>king</reg></choice> now so he has to kill <name type="person">Duncan</name>.</s>
        <s><name type="person">Macbeth</name> though if it's right to kill him so <name type="person">Lady Macbeth</name> wants to convince <name type="person">Macbeth</name> to do it.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>She makes a plan, how her husband can do it.</s>
        <s>She wants to invite <name type="person">Duncan</name> and his chamberlains.</s>
        <s><name type="person">Lady Macbeth</name> wants to make them drunk, so it is more easy for <name type="person">Macbeth</name> to kill <name type="person">Duncan</name>.</s>
        <s><name type="person">Macbeth</name> stays undecided, but he <choice><orig>know</orig><reg>knows</reg></choice> he must kill <name type="person">Duncan</name> at this evening to be the new <choice><orig>King</orig><reg>king</reg></choice>.</s>
      </p>
